      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 50.2</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 50.2</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>生之徒，</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>they enter (again) and die.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-050__align-003">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-050</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">3</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 50.3 - 老子 50.5</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 50.3</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>十有三；死之徒，十有三；</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Of every ten three are ministers of life (to themselves); and three are ministers of death.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-050__align-004">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-050</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">4</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 50.6 - 老子 50.9</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 50.4</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>人之生，動之死地，亦十有三。夫何故？</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>There are also three in every ten whose aim is to live, but whose movements tend to the land (or place) of death. And for what reason?</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-050__align-005">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-050</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">4</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">2</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 50.10 - 老子 50.13</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 50.5 - 老子 50.6</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>以其生生之厚。蓋聞善攝生者，陸行不遇兕虎，入軍不被甲兵；</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Because of their excessive endeavours to perpetuate life. But I have heard that he who is skilful in managing the life entrusted to him for a time travels on the land without having to shun rhinoceros or tiger, and enters a host without having to avoid buff coat or sharp weapon.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-050__align-006">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-050</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">4</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 50.14 - 老子 50.17</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 50.7</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>兕無所投其角，虎無所措其爪，兵無所容其刃。夫何故？</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The rhinoceros finds no place in him into which to thrust its horn, nor the tiger a place in which to fix its claws, nor the weapon a place to admit its point. And for what reason?</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="laozi-chapter-050__align-007">
      <prop type="x-work-id">laozi</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">laozi-chapter-050</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">chapter</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">sentence</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">grouped</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">老子 50.18</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">老子 50.8</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>以其無死地。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Because there is in him no place of death.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
